# imane Mobile App - Environment Configuration
# ==================================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# NEVER commit .env or .env.production to version control!

# Google Maps Platform API Keys
# ------------------------------
# Get your API keys from: https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis
#
# IMPORTANT: Create separate API keys for development and production
# - Development key: Unrestricted or restricted to development bundle ID
# - Production key: Restricted to production bundle ID (jp.imane.app)
#
# Required APIs to enable:
# - Maps SDK for iOS
# - Places API (New)
# - Geocoding API

# Development API Key (used by run-dev-*.sh scripts)
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_DEV=your-development-google-maps-api-key-here

# Production API Key (used by build-prod.sh script)
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_PROD=your-production-google-maps-api-key-here

# Backend API Configuration
# -------------------------
# For development, these are set automatically by scripts:
# - run-dev-simulator.sh uses http://localhost:8000/api/v1
# - run-dev-device.sh uses http://${API_HOST}:8000/api/v1

# For production builds, override if needed:
# PROD_API_URL=https://your-production-api.com/api/v1

# Optional: Development device IP (for run-dev-device.sh)
# API_HOST=192.168.0.14

# ==============================================
# Setup Instructions
# ==============================================
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Get Google Maps API keys:
#    - Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#    - Enable Maps SDK for iOS, Places API (New), and Geocoding API
#    - Create two API keys (development and production)
#    - Add them to GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_DEV and GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_PROD
#
# 3. (Optional) For production-only configuration:
#    cp .env.example .env.production
#    # Then add only production keys to .env.production
#
# 4. Run the app:
#    ./scripts/run-dev-simulator.sh  # Development mode
#    ./scripts/build-prod.sh          # Production build
#
# ==============================================
# Security Notes
# ==============================================
#
# - NEVER commit .env or .env.production files
# - Use different API keys for dev and prod
# - Restrict production API keys to your bundle ID
# - Rotate keys regularly
# - Monitor usage in Google Cloud Console
#
